    <p class="text-gray-300">1: Write  <span class="math">\\mathbf{c}</span>  as  <span class="math">\\ell</span>  finite field elements  <span class="math">c_{1},\\ldots ,c_{\\ell}</span>  where  <span class="math">c_{i}\\in \\mathbb{F}_{p}</span> 2: if  <span class="math">\\ell \\geq p / 2</span>  then return  <span class="math">\\perp</span> . 3:  <span class="math">\\Sigma \\gets 0</span> 4: for  <span class="math">i = 1, \\lfloor \\ell / 2 \\rfloor</span>  do 5:  <span class="math">m_{2\\cdot i - 1}\\gets c_{2\\cdot i} - \\widetilde{\\mathsf{E}}_{\\mathbf{k}}^{2\\cdot i,N}(c_{2\\cdot i - 1})</span> 6:  <span class="math">m_{2\\cdot i}\\gets c_{2\\cdot i - 1} - \\widetilde{\\mathsf{E}}_{\\mathbf{k}}^{2\\cdot i - 1,N}(m_{2\\cdot i - 1})</span> 7:  <span class="math">\\Sigma \\gets \\Sigma + m_{2\\cdot i}</span> 8: if  <span class="math">\\ell</span>  is odd then 9:  <span class="math">m_{\\ell}\\gets c_{\\ell} - \\widetilde{\\mathsf{E}}_{\\mathbf{k}}^{\\ell ,N}(0)</span> 10:  <span class="math">\\Sigma \\gets \\Sigma + m_{\\ell}</span> 11:  <span class="math">\\mathbf{m} \\gets (m_1, \\dots, m_\\ell)</span> 12: Tag'  <span class="math">\\leftarrow \\widetilde{\\mathsf{E}}_{\\mathbf{k}}^{-\\ell ,N}(\\Sigma)</span> 13: if  <span class="math">\\mathsf{Tag}^{\\prime} = \\mathsf{Tag}</span>  then 14: return m 15: return  <span class="math">\\perp</span></p>

